      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 179,
      "message": "All this seems painful, and I think you have a bunch of other more complicated policy types to write the same code.   May be we could reconsider I move back the work I was doing to the models, or common. so you could reuse it (note today I just moved it to the drools-pdp from models after meet).   In any case, if you were to reuse the framework I mentioned, validation of types per field, presence of required, regex values validation, and conversion to a domain model would be one line of code.  In case of errors will give you a list of faulty locations so you could send back to the client.   If interested, check the junits in this review https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/policy/drools-pdp/+/100968/ and see if it fits these needs.",
